<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Most Europeans know several languages - I'm one of them. Dutch is my native language, besides that I'm also fluent in English. I can understand French and German.<P>However, (and no offense to the french people here, my apologies for the generalisation) the french are also known to be one of the most stubborn people in Europe, since they refuse to speak anything but french. They can speak english if they absolutely have to, but will speak french if they can get away with it.<P>Personally, I think everyone should be able to converse with their friends in his or her native language. However, when /ooc and /shout on a server (Karana specifically) is comprised of 90% french, then that can get irritating. Seeing as how not everyone understands french, and seeing as how it can be confusing. <P>One thing to note; I have made a few french friends who do speak english if that is required (i.e. a group member not understanding french). It's perfectly alright if a 100% french group speaks french exclusively, hey, I would too (if I were french, that is).<P>What I don't like, is that some groups of french speakers, do not allow any non-french speakers to join their groups - or boot them out if they find out that they have to speak english. Now, that's not so cool. <P>Just my 2cp<P>--------------------<P>--<BR>Xirian Ghostwalker<BR>Karana Server
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
