<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Ok, not that my opinion really counts for much, but here it is anyway  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>I have seen this general topic raised before, but Verant doesnt take action as only 1 group poses it at any one time.  Below are ideas (some mine, some stolen from other posts, some mix of mine/stolen idea):<P>1)  Make 1 server for each "main" country or language that can support it (ex:  German, French, Chinese, Japanese, Korean, etc).<P>2)  Make a server for a region if 1 country alone cannot support it (German/French, Asian, etc).<P>3)  Make a few servers tied more to "time zones" (Australia, etc).<P>4)  When Verant "shuts down" to patch (say 6am to 2 pm) "shut down" these other servers for the appropriate time zone for THEIR time (eg the French server would be patched from 6am to 2 pm FRENCH local time).<P>EQ is truley an internation game, and I have seen some "Korean only" guilds, etc.  Seems there is a large enough player base to support these other servers, and I see no harm in someone playing in a environment where most speak their language.  I sometimes play at odd hours, so I know what its like (I was in a group where 5 spoke Chinese and I didnt).<P>What I think you need to do Mayasej is hope someone with the know how can get a drive or petition going to make this happen.  Verant doesnt even have to make new servers, just make an "old server" the new "French" server, etc.  Let all the peeps of the country in question /movelog their characters to the new "country" server  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  Us "Yanks" can move our chars to another or stay on for a cultural experience  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Burzug Ironfyst, Paladin, Rodcet Nife<BR>"It is an honour to serve others"
