Nothing wrong with cultural identification, but when it goes too far it goes too far  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Hey, I identify with my culture and upbringing too - but you won't see me stubbornly speaking Dutch to people all the time. I speak English because I have to if people want to understand me, and even if I'm in Holland and I have English friends over, I speak English as a courtesy to my friends.<P>I find that aspect lacking in EQ. Whenever I join a group and I see French spoken, I ask if they can please stick to English - the reason for that is simple, my French is alright, but I don't understand shorthand or slang French. So how am I supposed to know if someone just pulled a huge train or whether they're just joking about that Ogre scratching his butt? <P>That translation thing Verant is working on would probably solve most of those problems though  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>--<BR>Xirian Ghostwalker<BR>Karana Server
