As I read these posts.. I realize some of you have some very valid points but (you knew there was going to be a but huh ) but....You have stated there are 600,000 words in the English language.. in that you would be approximately correct. English is not the dominant language in EQ though, the american dialect is the dominant language. The americans have over 1.5 million words in their language.. granted their words that are borrowed from many other cultures. <BR>The US was created by mixing many races,cultures and languages together. Though we all eventually ended up speaking english each culture brought their own to it and as the new millenium verges we have realized that the language we speak today in the US is very differant than the English that is spoke in Europe. <BR>So stating that French is more versatile than English because there are more words in their dictionary is not applicable when your referring to a game that uses American as its core dialect.<BR>And if you want to argue symantics go ask an Englishman if those Americans speak english.
