Jayde is correct, most people do speak American.  Though not officially a language it is almost an insult to the English for them to still call it English.<BR>This is probably where all the contractions and phoenetiscism comes from (phat lewt, plz, NP, etc...).  Such things are used less often in England, and though we have regional accents, the written word is consistent throughout due to the rules applied to it (which, if I'm not mistaken, have been partially removed in some American states).<BR>Anyway having a server for the Frnch would be discriminatig unless they put in a server for the Germans and the Italians and the Spanish and the Russians and the Azerbaijanis and anyone else with a language.  Possibly for every dialect in India and all those bloody Arab tongues, there is just no way that it is realistic to expect Verant to cover the cost of such an endeavor (without raising the subscription fees anyway!).  So if you want all the French (or whatever) in the same place, make a post on every message board you see about Everquest, telling them where to go (i.e. which server).<BR>Otherwise give up, "it ain't goin' ta hap'n."<P>--------------------<P>Chelack accepts no liability whatsoever for anything, regardless of whether he was directly involved or not.
