whoever said that every linguist agrees that each combination of letters in the english language is only correctly pronounced one way is totally and completely wrong.  we would not have long and short vowels, or an epsilon and an e, and upsilon and an o, an iota and an i, a schwa and and e and an a and an o in the international phonetic alphabet if that was true.  we would not have a theta and an edh to represent the different sounds a th makes in the words breathe and breath.  i just finished my linguist requirement in my english major and i can tell you, words in english have different pronounciations in different parts of the country that are correct, and and combo of letters can be correctly pronounced in many ways.  the words read and read are easy proof of that one.<P><BR>and the french server thing...  ideally, itd be wonderful..but there are too many different languages for and american company to be able to afford to care about.  its all about the almight dollar sign, whatever language you speak<P>--------------------<P>Auroradae<BR>20th Cleric of Tunare<BR>Karana<BR>Member of Void Of Chaos
